12:16.103 --> 12:17.602
You're not alone.

12:17.604 --> 12:19.771
Both Zagat
and Consumer Reports surveys

12:19.773 --> 12:23.274
have found that excessive noise
is the top complaint diners have

12:23.276 --> 12:27.245
before even service, crowds,
or even screwing up
your dang order

12:27.247 --> 12:28.913
by forgetting
your tater tots.

12:28.915 --> 12:32.083
A study by the New York Times
even found that some restaurants

12:32.085 --> 12:34.986
(metal screeching)
were louder
than a G.D. subway tunnel.

12:34.988 --> 12:37.856
That's so loud that it can cause
hearing damage.

12:37.858 --> 12:41.960
So, why are restaurants
so dang loud?

12:41.962 --> 12:45.630
One guy we can blame
is Chef Mario Francesco Batali.

12:45.632 --> 12:48.566
Yes, that Mario Batali.

12:48.568 --> 12:50.535
The same one who was accused
of sexual assault

12:50.537 --> 12:53.638
and responded with
a cinnamon roll recipe.

12:53.640 --> 12:55.840
Batali, first pumped loud music
into the dining room

12:55.842 --> 12:58.343
